===Etymology===
Appearing in the [[w:Muromachi_period|Muromachi period]] (1337 to 1573).

From older adjectival noun {{term|lang=ja|大き|tr=ōki}}, derived from attributive form ''ōki'' of cognate adjective ''ōshi'' (meaning both “large” or “many”, spelled as {{l|ja|多し}} or {{l|ja|大し}}, modern {{etyl|ja|-}} {{term|lang=ja|多い|tr=ōi||many}}), in turn derived from {{etyl|ojp|ja|sort=おおきい}} adjectival noun ''opo'' (“indistinct; of uncertain size, shape, or amount”; read as ''ō'' in modern {{etyl|ja|-}}, spelled as {{l|ja|凡}} or {{l|ja|大}}).

